	   <tr><td colspan=2>Trust me friend, shamans are far more powerful using spells then trying to melee.&nbsp;&nbsp;Try to melee a mob in velious that dual-wields and double attacks for 110 each.  That gives you about three rounds to do meager damage.  The only reason we shaman can get away with alittle more melee then the other casters is only because some dink goofed our class up and they just are too lazy to fix us.  "Hence the "New" class, or shaman done-right"  Ack!  Sorry!  Almost forgot the rest of my message.  The stats are great for a belt.  The belt I currently use is only 3 wis or so ands 4 more is always welcome.  The mana is great, because shamans get that lower wisdom problem and high mana spells.  The haste is great for tanking weenie-greenies for that skin or pelt or whatever you need from them.<br>&nbsp;<br>&lt;A HREF="<a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=168645"&gt;Tainwulf" target=_new>http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=168645"&gt;Tainwulf</a> Silverwolf&lt;/A&gt; <br>51 Mystic<br>Druzzil Ro<br>"Legends=Bad"</td></tr>
