	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, as a necro that actually melee's, I could certainly use this item to replace my FBSS.&nbsp;&nbsp;I know, but don't laugh!  My guild and I have this tactic.  We have a shaman, a bard, and myself in a group.  I prepare myself by getting out my Tserrina's Staff, load up Vamp Embrace, and get Regrowth+Haste+Dex casted on me.  Bard starts singing the heal song, Shaman slows the mob, I cast Bond of Death, and then jump in and melee.  With Slow and all the regen effects and my now 66pt drain tap(spell) and 55pt drain tap(spell) and pet taunting, I can usually hold aggro and never really lose life.  This saves the healer from using mana on heals and lets any other group members basically do dmg.  Necros may not have the best armour or the most hps or the best absorption of damage, but done right we can control the expenditure of mana.  And thru that, the rate at which a group pulls.  No mana, no heals, no pulls.  Once, in Howling Stones, our cleric almost fell asleep because he didn't have to heal and didn't know what to do.<br><br>A belt like this would help me do something like this.  Time to visit Chardok, I think ;)<br><br>Malkavia<br>Quellious<br>54 necro<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
