	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually there is meaning behind this belt. I was once beat out by a shaman in Lguk for a FBSS and atm I was pretty upset that a caster was getting a belt which I really could use in order to help keep the taunt on me being the warrior. But I was later informed, and eventually schooled in the fact that some casters use haste to help them. Shamans tank more than any other caster race and with a haste belt, the simple act of hitting the enemy more times, leads to stunning or knocking back the enemy more, so as to make the mob hit them less often and not as hard. Its wierd to think about but when I watched it happen, it seemed to actually work. This means that by making the enemy hit less often, its easier for the shammy to pull off some castes. By making a haste belt geared toward casters, I hope this will ease the load off off high lvl casters campin for FBSS's for themselves, and also I hope it opens some eyes that haste isnt necissarily only for the melee classes, other classes can benefit from its proc just as much.<br>52 Champion of Xev<br>&nbsp;<br>If winners never quit, and quitters never win... Who the hell came up with the phrase quit while your ahead?</td></tr>
